Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:23.46,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(298,0)}We sigh whenever we're about to come to a standstill
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.46,0:00:29.71,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}While moving on this endless journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.80,0:00:37.43,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Everytime we lunge for it, it escapes and flies off.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:44.85,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}But now, there's nothing to be afraid of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:52.78,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}The powerful ties that bind our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.78,0:00:58.24,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Will never come loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.28,0:01:07.96,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9}After a lifetime of searching, we finally arrived
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.96,0:01:13.76,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Here, where the period lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.92,0:01:23.06,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}Let's change all our sorrow and rage to power.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.06,0:01:27.98,OP04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,298}Destiny is right within our reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:23.46,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(298,0)}終わりなき旅の途中　立ち止まりそうな時
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.46,0:00:29.71,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}深いため息こぼす　僕らは
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.80,0:00:37.43,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}掴みかけてはまた離れていった
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:44.85,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}でも今はもう何も恐れることはない
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:52.78,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}心を繋ぐ強い絆は
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.78,0:00:58.24,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}けして解けはしないさ
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.28,0:01:07.96,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9}探し続けて辿り着いた
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.96,0:01:13.76,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}この場所で {\fsp8}Perio{\fsp3.2}d に
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.92,0:01:23.06,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}悲しみ怒り 力に変えて
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.06,0:01:27.98,OP04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,298}運命はすぐそばに
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:23.46,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(298,0)}Owarinaki tabi no tochuu tachidomarisouna toki
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.46,0:00:29.71,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Fukai tameiki kobosu bokura wa
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.80,0:00:37.43,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Tsukamikaketewa mata hanareteitta
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:44.85,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Demo ima wa mou nanimo osoreru koto wa nai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:52.78,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}Kokoro wo tsunagu tsuyoi kizuna wa
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.78,0:00:58.24,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Keshite hodoke wa shinai sa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.28,0:01:07.96,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9}Sagashitsuzukete tadoritsuita
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.96,0:01:13.76,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,398}Kono basho de piriodo ni
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.92,0:01:23.06,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(398,0}Kanashimi ikari chikara ni kaete
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.06,0:01:27.98,OP04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be9\fad(0,298}Unmei wa sugu soba ni
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.25,0:22:45.21,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}The promise we never made
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.21,0:22:46.01,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}yet again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.01,0:22:50.84,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}tries to snatch our future away from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.47,0:22:56.43,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it that we can't rejoice
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.43,0:22:57.43,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}straight from the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:23:02.40,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}when we obtain something we've always been after?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.06,0:23:08.11,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,498}The overflowing tears aren't from feebleness or remorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.78,0:23:12.91,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,258)}They're fragments born from agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.58,0:23:17.95,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Of all the moments and destinies,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.95,0:23:26.71,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}I realized there's one absolute certainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.71,0:23:29.26,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if things get tough and I'm at my limit
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.26,0:23:33.26,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:38.14,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don't let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.14,0:23:45.98,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}I can feel the warmth of your right hand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.98,0:23:49.65,ED04 Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}where it's tightly joined with my left.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.25,0:22:45.21,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}交わしたはずのない約束が
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.21,0:22:46.01,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}今日も
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.01,0:22:50.84,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}僕らの未来を奪おうとする
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.47,0:22:56.43,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,欲しがっていたものを手にしても
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.43,0:22:57.43,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}素直に
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:23:02.40,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}うまく笑えないのはなぜだろう
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.06,0:23:08.11,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,498}あふれる涙は　弱さや後悔じゃない
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.78,0:23:12.91,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,258)}イタミが生んだカケラで
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.58,0:23:17.95,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}どんな瞬間だって運命だって
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.95,0:23:26.71,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}ひとつだけ確かなものがあると知った
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.71,0:23:29.26,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,限界だって困難だって
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.26,0:23:33.26,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,あきらめたくないよ
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:38.14,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,このまま離さないで
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.14,0:23:45.98,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}かたく握りしめた　君の右手のぬくもり
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.98,0:23:49.65,ED04 Kana,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}ここにあるから
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.25,0:22:45.21,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Kawashita hazu no nai yakasoku ga
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.21,0:22:46.01,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Kyou mo
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.01,0:22:50.84,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}Bokura no mirai wo ubaou to suru
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.47,0:22:56.43,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshigatteita mono wo te ni shitemo
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.43,0:22:57.43,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Sunao ni
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.43,0:23:02.40,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}Umaku waraenai nowa nazedarou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.06,0:23:08.11,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,498}Afureru namida wo yowasa ya koukai ja nai
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.78,0:23:12.91,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,258)}Itami ga unda kakera de
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.58,0:23:17.95,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Donna shunkan datte unmei datte
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.95,0:23:26.71,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Hitotsu dake tashika na mono ga aru to shitta
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.71,0:23:29.26,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkai datte konnan datte
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.26,0:23:33.26,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,Akirametakunaiyo
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:38.14,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,Konomama hanasanaide
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.14,0:23:45.98,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13}Kataku nigirishimeta kimi no migite no nukumori
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.98,0:23:49.65,ED04 Roma,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be13\fad(0,498)}Koko ni arukara
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.66,0:01:41.41,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost like a maze in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.83,0:01:43.37,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Try not to get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.37,0:01:44.45,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.25,0:01:49.46,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Oww...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.87,0:01:50.08,Default-alt,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.29,0:01:51.63,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.84,0:01:56.92,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.55,0:01:59.26,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dynamite!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.26,0:02:00.26,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.51,0:02:04.68,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,They're all damp now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.14,0:02:07.48,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry; they won't explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.56,0:02:10.85,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Come on; get a move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:13.65,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know when the enemy will come after us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.57,0:02:15.44,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.62,0:02:23.28,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the blizzard died down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.20,0:02:26.25,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.25,0:02:27.12,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.37,0:02:34.63,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to take down Kimblee and his\Ntwo men from Central when we see an opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.96,0:02:37.88,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.65,0:02:55.73,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to proceed with the mission with only the men currently present.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.19,0:02:58.61,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell anyone; not even soldiers from Northern Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.61,0:02:59.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey-
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.15,0:03:00.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Major Miles!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.82,0:03:02.91,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,By "bring down", do you mean you're going to kill them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:04.91,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.45,0:03:07.37,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't approve killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.70,0:03:10.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's better to seal their abilities and beat information out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.58,0:03:13.08,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think he'll tell the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.08,0:03:15.04,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous to keep him alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.04,0:03:16.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about his men?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.80,0:03:21.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,They may also be obeying him without choice after being turned into chimeras!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.26,0:03:26.22,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You have a point, but the keyword here is {\i1}"may"{\i0\fscx100}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.76,0:03:29.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So you're going to kill them simply based on suspicion?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.39,0:03:32.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Same with Lieutenant General Raven! There were plenty of other methods-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.85,0:03:34.90,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Do not forget the law of Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:36.86,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,If you let your guard down, you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.69,0:03:43.11,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Your softness may come back to kill you or one of your friends someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.78,0:03:49.45,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need careless men in this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.45,0:03:52.75,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to get rid of Kimblee and his two men.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.59,0:04:00.71,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he's still a kid, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.71,0:04:01.97,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.97,0:04:05.64,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to settle matters without deaths in this world is a soft idea in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.05,0:04:08.76,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But there was a time I was like that, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:11.27,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I was, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.85,0:04:15.52,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,You start to understand once you reach this age after living through many battles...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.90,0:04:19.78,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,...that it's more difficult to keep someone alive rather than killing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.61,0:04:24.24,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,The Elric Brothers chose the tougher path.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.36,0:04:27.24,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Strange guys, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.24,0:04:27.87,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.33,0:04:30.54,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm also a bit envious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.50,0:04:41.00,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,What's this "Rasayana" he writes about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.00,0:04:43.26,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,It's used to describe a miraculous medicine that extends one's lifespan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.88,0:04:47.18,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if he's talking about a philosopher's stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:48.39,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.39,0:04:56.27,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,What is this "Aurelian" that "turns all metal to gold,\Nand transforms old men to adolescents"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.85,0:04:58.02,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,It's a word for gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.48,0:05:01.69,Default,Marco,0000,0000,0000,,Most of this talks about immortality and gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.69,0:05:07.41,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be because Mr. Scar's brother was heavily influenced by Eastern Alchemy from Xing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.82,0:05:09.07,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.07,0:05:14.00,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,In my country, we refer to the immortal as a "True Being".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.00,0:05:19.17,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,It literally means "Perfect Being",\Nbut because gold is a perfect metal,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.17,0:05:22.25,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,there are times we refer to\Na "True Being" as a "Golden Being".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:29.51,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So a perfect being is a golden being.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.85,0:05:33.89,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Some say we refer to them that way because\Nthe person who introduced alchemy to Xing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.89,0:05:39.77,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,...was an immortal man with golden hair and eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.77,0:05:41.15,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.98,0:05:45.99,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Golden hair and eyes? Sounds like Ed and Al!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.99,0:05:48.45,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Hey guys, come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:49.24,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,I found the exit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.79,0:05:59.29,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,The sun's so bright!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.75,0:06:01.96,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we were able to get through the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.29,0:06:03.75,Default,Jerso,0000,0000,0000,,The weather looks nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.09,0:06:06.38,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head to Briggs now while we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.38,0:06:08.80,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, everyone. Follow me-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.09,0:06:11.97,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the snow is pretty deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.97,0:06:13.97,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,You can ride on my back, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.56,0:06:18.85,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,We'll make a path through the snow, so you can follow us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.85,0:06:20.31,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,We appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.30,0:06:11.47,Default-alt,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.47,0:06:12.93,Default-alt,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.93,0:06:14.39,Default-alt,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.72,0:06:16.35,Default-alt,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,You guys listening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.35,0:06:17.81,Default-alt,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.81,0:06:20.31,Default-alt,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.53,0:06:31.66,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.66,0:06:34.79,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Help me!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.12,0:06:37.29,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Is someone there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.29,0:06:38.21,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.50,0:06:40.29,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Alphonse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.83,0:06:41.83,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no, oh no, oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.83,0:06:43.29,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Al?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.42,0:06:46.71,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You saved me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.09,0:06:50.22,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I got stuck in a deep spot and ended up getting buried by the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.22,0:06:51.89,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But why are you here, Al?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.14,0:06:55.60,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I crossed the mountain to get here before you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.60,0:06:58.77,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,You crossed the mountain... in that blizzard?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.23,0:07:04.94,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,I get it. Instead of making a detour here, you took a straight path.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:07.44,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,But why make such a reckless trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.44,0:07:09.32,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I have urgent news.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.32,0:07:10.82,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,"Urgent news"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.78,0:07:14.95,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The Central Army has infiltrated Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.49,0:07:20.66,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, Major General Armstrong has been summoned to Central, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.66,0:07:24.04,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,So it's dangerous to go there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.09,0:07:27.30,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.30,0:07:29.59,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,We can't go back, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.13,0:07:33.09,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to have to find somewhere else to hide out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.09,0:07:35.14,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, like where?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.98,0:07:42.02,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.44,0:07:43.98,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.52,0:07:48.48,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,There should be a village by the name of Asbec not too far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.15,0:07:53.36,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard rumors my fellow countrymen have taken refuge in the slums there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.36,0:07:55.70,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,An Ishbalan slum, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.70,0:07:58.08,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't seem like we have much of a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.45,0:08:00.50,Default,Yoki,0000,0000,0000,,Master, you rock! Let's get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.33,0:08:07.21,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But is it going to be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.21,0:08:08.25,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.25,0:08:12.05,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Won't Sir Kimblee get suspicious if you disappear all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.05,0:08:15.97,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing to worry about. Brother will keep everything under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.55,0:08:19.06,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Three from the third squadron.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.60,0:08:21.06,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Five from the fourth squadron.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.68,0:08:23.10,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.48,0:08:26.65,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I want you all to begin searching in the districts you've been assigned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.65,0:08:27.11,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.11,0:08:28.02,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.61,0:08:33.45,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Let's move.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.45,0:08:34.74,Default,Mick,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.82,0:08:37.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Alphonse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.82,0:08:39.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this where you say "Okay"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.74,0:08:45.37,Default,Mick,0000,0000,0000,,But it's really hard to move in this, Edward.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.37,0:08:47.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's where I need you to do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.42,0:08:49.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Kimblee's watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.25,0:08:52.01,Default,Mick,0000,0000,0000,,Wait up, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.01,0:08:53.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Walk faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.02,0:09:05.02,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Where are Kimblee and company searching?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.02,0:09:07.81,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,There's a huge mine shaft at the center of the town, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.81,0:09:10.82,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, they're going to enter that and search the mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.11,0:09:18.07,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He said he's only going to take the men he brought from Central because he doesn't trust the soldiers up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.74,0:09:21.99,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,He must have noticed already.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.49,0:09:23.45,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to stall them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.83,0:09:26.46,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Secure a position for sniping near the shaft mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.46,0:09:26.96,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.13,0:09:39.64,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Search the entrance to the mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.64,0:09:42.35,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,If you find multiple footprints, there's no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.35,0:09:42.89,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.81,0:09:48.77,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.77,0:09:50.81,Default,Mick,0000,0000,0000,,At this distance, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.69,0:09:56.28,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.86,0:09:58.32,Default,Mick,0000,0000,0000,,Edward is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.32,0:09:59.03,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:10.50,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee, shouldn't you leave it to the soldiers from Briggs to search the mines?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.50,0:10:13.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it's a labyrinth down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.50,0:10:18.97,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing as how you went through the effort to persuade me out of it, this must be the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.97,0:10:20.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.01,0:10:22.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to capture Scar-
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:26.60,Default-alt,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Or are you trying to buy time to position the sniper?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.02,0:10:29.60,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So you noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.19,0:10:33.65,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,There's so much thirst for blood in the atmosphere; it would be odd {\i1}not{\i0\fscx30} {\r} to notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.07,0:10:36.90,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't survive Ishbal for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.90,0:10:40.74,Default,Mick,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like they're talking about something. What should I do, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.53,0:10:43.33,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Can you try to adjust your aim on Kimblee?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.33,0:10:44.16,Default,Mick,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.16,0:10:46.45,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Do it. Be very careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.45,0:10:47.29,Default,Mick,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.26,0:11:01.51,Default,Mick,0000,0000,0000,,That bastard hid himself in snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.51,0:11:02.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.10,0:11:06.22,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Kimblee!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.14,0:11:09.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.41,0:11:29.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So you two are chimeras, too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.11,0:12:06.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shit... I can't see a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.20,0:12:08.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they can't see me either...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.66,0:12:09.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...so I guess we're even-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.45,0:12:14.71,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Quit resisting, Fullmetal Alchemist!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.50,0:12:20.13,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way for you to run since we can track you by scent!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.13,0:12:21.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.77,0:12:31.73,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Fullmetal!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.73,0:12:34.89,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.60,0:12:37.36,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?! Respond!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.36,0:12:39.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Major Miles?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.11,0:12:40.69,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There are chimeras here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.69,0:12:43.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And they've been trained to fight in places with low visibility!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.57,0:12:46.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Stay out of the smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.50,0:12:58.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oww...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.46,0:13:01.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit... that just made me shorter...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.30,0:13:04.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dynamite?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.80,0:13:07.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're in a mine, all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.89,0:13:14.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get too close now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.43,0:13:16.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You do know what these are, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.27,0:13:17.56,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,Are you stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.56,0:13:20.61,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,Those are probably too damp to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.61,0:13:24.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Do you two know what dynamite is made of?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.36,0:13:26.86,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,Nitroglycerine?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.86,0:13:30.37,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,Nitroglycol, chips of wood, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.37,0:13:32.45,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,...ammonium nitrate, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.45,0:13:36.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's ammonium nitrate made of?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.75,0:13:39.38,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,Easy! Nitric acid and ammonia-
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.30,0:13:44.21,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Ammonia?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.42,0:13:49.51,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,The smell!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.93,0:13:57.39,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,What's that smell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.39,0:13:58.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ammonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.94,0:14:01.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there's a downside to having too keen a sense of smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.86,0:14:04.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,These guys are toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.19,0:14:09.70,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,So this is how you're going to act as soon as your hostages are released?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.70,0:14:11.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.99,0:14:16.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just here to beat all the information you know out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.29,0:14:19.67,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Christ, you're so hot-blooded.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.04,0:14:24.05,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting with a young man like yourself during\Nmy convalescence would surely break my bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:27.63,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't have time to play with you either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.30,0:14:31.80,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll be using this, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.26,0:14:34.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He just saved me the trouble of searching for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.27,0:14:40.14,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,He's fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.28,0:14:49.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.16,0:14:58.08,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He lost his philosopher's stone,\Nand his transmutation circle is no longer useable!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.54,0:14:59.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.25,0:15:00.33,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,"I win!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.04,0:15:02.29,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you're thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.25,0:15:05.21,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,The determination not to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.55,0:15:07.63,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,An admirable policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.63,0:15:11.80,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,But that's just asking for your enemy to take advantage of you during battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.39,0:15:16.85,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,You should have killed me at that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.31,0:15:23.61,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,That softness is the cause of your defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.10,0:16:04.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Did I fall down the mine shaft?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.02,0:16:10.86,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,He's so heartless... he even got us into it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.86,0:16:12.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oww...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.45,0:16:13.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.82,0:16:15.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Kimblee go...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:23.67,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You've got to be kidding me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.67,0:16:24.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:50.27,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al! What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.27,0:16:52.07,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Alphonse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.07,0:16:52.86,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.57,0:16:55.57,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.03,0:16:57.78,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm being drawn again...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.78,0:17:01.37,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, "being drawn"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.91,0:17:02.58,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.54,0:17:02.58,Default-alt,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.50,0:17:04.71,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,My soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.42,0:17:07.63,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...is being drawn toward...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.67,0:17:11.63,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.63,0:17:12.46,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.46,0:17:14.59,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,His soul is being drawn?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.59,0:17:18.26,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Has this happened before?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.26,0:17:19.30,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\alpha&HFF&}PLACEHOLDER
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.01,0:17:20.89,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.05,0:17:14.59,Default-alt,May,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Alphonse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.59,0:17:17.76,Default-alt,May,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Alphonse! Pull yourself together!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:20.89,Default-alt,May,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Alphonse!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.89,0:17:23.47,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up, Al!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.89,0:17:24.81,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.81,0:17:25.52,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.85,0:17:26.98,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.85,0:17:29.06,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.44,0:17:30.11,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.28,0:17:33.61,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ed!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.45,0:17:48.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I can't... let her cry over something stupid like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:08.35,Default,Hei,0000,0000,0000,,Damn that Kimblee...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.90,0:18:14.82,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Fullmetal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.82,0:18:15.94,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,You alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.65,0:18:18.70,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you save us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.70,0:18:20.87,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,You're hurt far worse than us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.62,0:18:24.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't... get the wrong idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.12,0:18:29.58,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I... need someone to pull...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.58,0:18:32.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...this thing out... of my abdomen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.25,0:18:36.05,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,You're asking us to pull that steel frame out of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.05,0:18:37.72,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,We're technically enemies, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.72,0:18:39.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.85,0:18:47.77,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we weren't ordered to kill you or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.77,0:18:49.89,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:54.69,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,But if we pull that out,\Nyou're going to bleed out in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.15,0:19:01.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as it leaves my body... I'm going to seal the wound... before I bleed to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.70,0:19:06.20,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,Are you experienced in medical alchemy at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.54,0:19:13.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've attempted human transmutation in the past... so I studied the main points.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.42,0:19:17.88,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,"The main points"? I'm pretty sure your organs are shredded to pieces...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.88,0:19:21.05,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't have a philosopher's stone like Sir Kimblee does...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.93,0:19:26.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm going to use my life instead of a philosopher's stone...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.51,0:19:27.52,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.56,0:19:32.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It may shorten my life span by a bit, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.27,0:19:33.23,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,Is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.73,0:19:36.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have the time to dawdle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.15,0:19:42.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If this injury was caused by my softness... then I have to clean up after myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.87,0:19:48.37,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really get it, but you don't have much time to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.33,0:19:50.29,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pulling it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.42,0:19:58.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Do it, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.67,0:20:03.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I need to think of my life as a form of energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.52,0:20:11.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The same as... a philosopher's stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.90,0:20:17.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.06,0:20:21.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, I'm nothing more than\Na philosopher's stone made out of one soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.53,0:20:30.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Think back, and try to remember that feeling!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.45,0:20:32.79,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That feeling...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.96,0:20:34.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...of using...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.71,0:20:38.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...life!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:20:58.19,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,Is he dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.94,0:21:03.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't just write me off like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.03,0:21:05.28,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it worked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.82,0:21:08.16,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's not completely healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.74,0:21:16.37,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a temporary measure of linking the undamaged tissues... to stop the bleeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.67,0:21:19.00,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,Then we need to get you to a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:22.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't have time... for that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.92,0:21:24.55,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.55,0:21:26.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I need to go after Kimblee...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.05,0:21:30.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...else... everyone will be in danger...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.39,0:21:34.68,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.68,0:21:35.98,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.98,0:21:38.77,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he can win against him in this state.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.78,0:21:43.90,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.99,0:21:46.28,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.28,0:21:48.28,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,A philosopher's stone, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.28,0:21:50.32,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,The one Sir Kimblee had with him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.32,0:21:52.33,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to refer to that freak as "Sir".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.33,0:21:55.62,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,He dragged us into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.62,0:21:57.25,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.25,0:21:59.83,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's the last time we see that bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.83,0:22:01.00,Default,Hei,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.00,0:22:04.38,Default,Hei,0000,0000,0000,,People will think we died here, so we're free.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.21,0:22:07.84,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,And what should we do about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.34,0:22:11.72,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,We can't just let him die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.72,0:22:14.02,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,He saved our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.22,0:22:16.56,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,Well said.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.35,0:22:20.23,Default,Dar,0000,0000,0000,,We need to find a doctor right away\Nonce we get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.23,0:22:21.27,Default,Hein,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.87,0:24:04.17,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,After breaking the stalemate,\Nunforeseen ideas and actions open new paths.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.13,0:24:09.38,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The one to find the hidden truth obtains the key to victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.71,0:24:13.88,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,But that's all a part of the accumulating daily life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.64,0:24:19.18,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.18,0:24:22.73,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 42, Signs of a Counteroffensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.19,0:24:25.86,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The beginning of war.
